text.__SUMMARY__: Odostomia acutidens, common name the sharp-tooth odostome,  is a species of sea snail, a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Pyramidellidae, the pyrams and their allies.
text.Description: The shell grows to a length of  4 mm.
text.Distribution:
This species occurs in the following locations:
Gulf of Mexico (Florida)
